    • handleEvents

      public void handleEvents()
      Event handling happens in a following way: 1. Dequeue one by one all unhandled events from the unhandledEvents queue. 2. If there are some observers registered to listen to that event, then choose one of them randomly or add all of them depending on, whether all observers should be informed about the event and let him handle the event. 2.1 If the observer is a device, then ensure that the device is in the same room as the source of the event. 3. Mark the event as handled 4. Enqueue the events again which could not be handled by any observer.
